### Architecture Principles

**Modular Monolith for MVP.** The backend is structured as a monolith with clear module boundaries (Routes → Controller → Service). This is faster to build and deploy in 4 days, and the module separation means it can be decomposed into microservices when scaling demands it — without rewriting any business logic.

**Supabase as infrastructure, Prisma as interface.** Supabase hosts a managed PostgreSQL instance and provides file storage for profile photos. Prisma connects to Supabase as the ORM, providing type-safe queries, schema migrations, and clean data access patterns. This combination gives speed of setup (Supabase) with code quality (Prisma).

**Squad as the financial backbone.** Every financial event in the system — wallet creation, payment collection, fund transfer, withdrawal — routes through Squad API. The backend never holds money; Squad does. This means the platform is compliant and auditable from day one.

**AI as a feature, not infrastructure.** Claude is called at specific, well-defined touchpoints (search matching, credit insights, business tips). This keeps AI costs predictable, responses fast, and the system functional even if the AI layer is unavailable.

