## 5. Technology Stack — Full Justification

### Backend

| Technology | Decision | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| **Node.js + Express** | Primary framework | Async-first, huge ecosystem, fast to build, JSON-native. One developer can move fast. |
| **Supabase PostgreSQL** | Primary database | Free managed Postgres, instant setup, no DevOps needed, connection string works with Prisma. |
| **Prisma ORM** | Database interface | Type-safe queries, auto-generated migrations, readable schema definition, catches errors at compile time. |
| **Supabase Storage** | File storage | Free CDN-backed file storage for profile photos. Replaces Cloudinary. Integrated with the same Supabase project. |
| **Squad API** | Financial layer | Mandated by hackathon. Covers virtual accounts, collections, transfers, webhooks — everything needed. |
| **Anthropic Claude** | AI layer | Best-in-class natural language understanding. Handles matching, scoring insights, and business tips without a custom ML model. |
| **Termii** | SMS / OTP | Nigerian-focused SMS provider. More reliable delivery and cheaper rates than Twilio for Nigerian phone numbers. |
| **node-cron** | Background jobs | Lightweight scheduler for nightly score refresh and hourly escrow timeout, runs inside the Express process — no separate job server needed for MVP. |
| **Winston** | Logging | Structured logs to console in dev, file in production. Essential for debugging Squad webhook issues. |

### Frontend

| Technology | Decision | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| **Next.js 14** | Framework | **Not Vite.** Next.js App Router provides SSR for provider profile pages — critical for SEO so providers can be found via Google search. Vite is a pure SPA; Google sees blank HTML. |
| **Tailwind CSS** | Styling | Utility-first means no context-switching between CSS and JS. Fast to build, consistent spacing system, great mobile defaults. |
| **Zustand** | Global state | Auth user, wallet balance, UI state. Lighter and less boilerplate than Redux. Persists to localStorage for auth. |
| **TanStack Query** | Server state | Caching, background refetching, loading/error states, automatic stale-while-revalidate. Eliminates most useEffect/useState data fetching patterns. |
| **React Hook Form + Zod** | Forms | Uncontrolled inputs = no re-renders on keystroke. Zod schemas are shared with the backend, so frontend and backend validation are always in sync. |
