## 12. Credit Scoring System

The credit score is the core alternative data layer. It produces a number from 0 to 100 for every provider and maps it to a tier. No bank history is required.

### Scoring Formula

```
Total Score = (Jobs Score × 0.40)
            + (Earnings Score × 0.30)
            + (Rating Score × 0.20)
            + (Tenure Score × 0.10)
```

### Sub-Score Calculations

**Jobs Score (40% weight)**
```
Jobs Score = min(completedBookings / 50, 1) × 100
```
A provider who has completed 50 or more jobs gets a perfect jobs score. A provider with 10 jobs gets 20 points, contributing 8 points to the total score.

**Earnings Score (30% weight)**
```
Earnings Score = min(totalEarned / 500000, 1) × 100
```
₦500,000 in total earnings represents the cap for a perfect earnings score. A provider who has earned ₦100,000 gets 20 points, contributing 6 points to the total score.

**Rating Score (20% weight)**
```
Rating Score = ((avgRating - 1) / 4) × 100
```
Normalises the 1–5 star rating to a 0–100 scale. A provider with a 4.5 average gets 87.5 points, contributing 17.5 points to the total score.

**Tenure Score (10% weight)**
```
Tenure Score = min(accountAgeDays / 365, 1) × 100
```
An account that is 1 year or older gets a perfect tenure score. This rewards established providers and discourages fake accounts.

### Tier Thresholds

| Score Range | Tier | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| 0–24 | Bronze | New provider, building history |
| 25–49 | Silver | Established, consistent provider |
| 50–74 | Gold | High-performing, trusted provider |
| 75–100 | Platinum | Top-tier, eligible for financial products |

### When Scores Update

1. **Real-time:** Immediately after every `transfer.success` Squad webhook (a booking was just completed and paid)
2. **Nightly batch:** A cron job at 2:00 AM recalculates scores for all active providers — catches any edge cases missed by real-time updates

### Future Use of the Score (Phase 2)

The credit score is designed to be the entry point to formal financial products. A Platinum provider with ₦800,000 processed through the platform is a strong loan candidate even with no bank history. Phase 2 financial institution partners will access scores via a verified API, enabling:
- Microloans up to ₦500,000 for Gold and Platinum providers
- Savings products with preferential rates
- Parametric micro-insurance on bookings

